1. Open PowerShell

Go to your project:

cd C:\Users\User\Documents\leadscrapper
2. Start the backend

If you're using Docker (which you have been):

docker compose up -d postgres backend



Verify it's running:

docker ps

You should see containers similar to:

leadscrapper-backend
leadscrapper-postgres
3. Start the frontend

Open a second PowerShell window.

cd C:\Users\User\Documents\leadscrapper\frontend

Then run:

npm install

(Only the first time or after dependencies change.)

Then:

npm run dev

You should see something like:

Ready in 2.3s

Local:
http://localhost:3000
4. Open the application

Go to:

http://localhost:3000